      "content": "If you can walk around a little after a day or two, it's definitely a bad sprain. You don't need an X-ray unless you can't walk at all, but you should still see a doctor for a proper diagnosis and treatment plan. If the swelling doesn't go down, or if you can't walk, then you should definitely get an X-ray to rule out a fracture. But if you're feeling better, you can probably just stick with RICE and over-the-counter pain relievers. Just make sure to keep the ankle elevated and ice it regularly. And if you're still in pain after a few days, consider taking a few days off from running and other activities to let your ankle heal. Remember, it's important to listen to your body and not push yourself too hard.",
